article.description: — Jack Ferguson had 14 points to lead five Colgate players in double figures as the Raiders beat Army 76-57 on Monday night.
article.headline: Ferguson, Richardson carry Colgate past Army 76-57
article.linkText: Ferguson, Richardson carry Colgate past Army 76-57
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Jack Ferguson had 14 points to lead five Colgate players in double figures as the Raiders beat Army 76-57 on Monday night. Tucker Richardson added 13 points, Ryan Moffatt chipped in 12, Jeff Woodward scored 11 and Nelly Cummings had 10 for Colgate (5-10, 1-1 Patriot League). Richardson also had seven rebounds, while Woodward posted 10 rebounds, three assists and three blocks. Josh Caldwell had 16 points and six assists for the Black Knights (9-7, 3-1).
